    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a museum-quality example of the E46 chassis, featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double-VANOS variable valve timing. The powertrain is mated to a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox, delivering an analog driving experience that remains the industry benchmark. Mechanical highlights include a proactive rod bearing service, a reinforced rear subframe to ensure structural rigidity, and an M Variable Differential Lock for superior corner-exit traction. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec and tight, providing the telepathic steering feedback these cars are known for. Finished in impeccable paint with a pristine interior, this vehicle has been maintained to the highest standards of mechanical and aesthetic excellence.",
